<paragraph id="A44DAF3E9D4EFFE4FEEEFE94FCA9FE10" blockId="10.[264,1323,284,470]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Remarks. The brown vestiture of the body, brown patterns of the legs, wing venation, and the three white tomentose stripes on the pleuron of 
<taxonomicName id="63F2D4BD9D4EFFE4FC5BFECCFC3BFE9B" box="[909,1020,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypnus">
<emphasis id="9686732C9D4EFFE4FC5BFECCFC3BFE9B" box="[909,1020,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. hypnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="63F2D4BD9D4EFFE4FB75FECCFAECFE9B" box="[1187,1323,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Pygommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apoticius">
<emphasis id="9686732C9D4EFFE4FB75FECCFAECFE9B" box="[1187,1323,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. apoticius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="63F2D4BD9D4EFFE4FEECFEE4FE7FFE43" box="[314,440,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Pygommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="misamis">
<emphasis id="9686732C9D4EFFE4FEECFEE4FE7FFE43" box="[314,440,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">P. misamis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the brown fore coxa and trochanters, and in the characters of the male terminalia (see 
<bibRefCitation id="C063D2CF9D4EFFE4FDECFE1CFD23FE68" author="Oldroyd" box="[570,740,404,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="22" refString="Oldroyd, H. (1972) Robber flies (Diptera: Asilidae) of the Philippine Islands. Pacific Insects, 14, 201 - 337." type="journal article" year="1972">
Oldroyd 
<number id="123ABD199D4EFFE4FD71FE1CFD23FE68" box="[679,740,404,430]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1972.0">1972</number>
